                            </FooterDetails>
                            <Heading/>
                            <Paragraph>The United States Court of Federal Claims has
                                        jurisdiction over claims seeking money judgments against the
                                        United States. A claim must be founded upon the
                                        Constitution, an act of Congress, an Executive order, a
                                        contract with the United States, or Federal regulations.
                                        Judges are appointed by the President for 15-year terms,
                                        subject to Senate confirmation. Appeals are to the U.S.
                                        Court of Appeals for the Federal Circuit.</Paragraph>
                        </Detail>
                    </Details>
                </Activity>
